# Code style
- Use semicolons
- Use single quotes for strings
- Use PascalCase for type names
- Use camelCase for variable and function names

# Code structure
- Organize code into modules/files based on feature
- Put shared helpers/utilities in /lib folder
- Put main application logic in src/index.ts

# Naming conventions 
- Name files to reflect contents (e.g. helpers.ts)
- Name exports based on what they contain (e.g. getRandomInt)

# Framework
- Use Hono for server framework
- Use bun for bundling/build tool

# Testing
- Write tests with vitest
- Put tests in /tests folder
- Name test files *.test.ts

# Linting 
- Lint with ESLint
- Follow Airbnb style guide

# Formatting
- Format with Prettier
- Set print width to 80
- Use single quotes
- Print trailing commas

# EditorConfig
- Set indent style=space and size=2

# Syntax
- Use TypeScript
- Enforce strict mode

# Styling
- Use Tailwind for styling

# Optimization
- Use Bun to bundle final build
- Minify code on build